<p  style="color:white;font-weight: bold;">About DemoToy <%=version %></p>

<p  style="color:white;font-weight: normal;">This application is a simple Node.js application that is expected to run in a container deployed by kubernetes. It was created to help explore IBM CloudPak for Watson AIOps by allowing the user to simulate incidents on the demo applications.</p>
<p  style="color:white;font-weight: normal;">This app uses Bootstrap 4. All the files have been copied locally to this application so Internet connectivity is not required and can work in an air-gapped system.</p>
<p  style="color:white;font-weight: normal;">The app was written by by Niklaus Hirt (nikh@ch.ibm.com), very much based on the work done by Jim Conallen (jconallen@us.ibm.com) and is made available under the Apache 2.0 license. If you find any bugs, create an issue on the GitHub site, and we'll do what we can to fix.</p> 
            


         
